sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Client
    participant RM as ResourceManager
    participant NM as NodeManager
    participant AM as ApplicationMaster

    Client->>RM: Submit Application (Specify queue: root.prod.finance)
    RM->>RM: Queue Placement Policy validates and assigns queue
    RM->>NM: Launch Container #1 (ApplicationMaster JVM)
    NM->>AM: Start AM JVM
    AM->>RM: Register ApplicationMaster (RegisterApplicationMasterRequest)
    
    loop Resource Negotiation
        AM->>RM: Resource Allocation Request (AllocateRequest: Memory, CPU, Locality)
        NM->>RM: Heartbeat (Resource status: Memory free, CPU free)
        Note over RM: Scheduler evaluates Queue Allocation tree
        RM->>AM: Resource Allocation Response (AllocateResponse: Container Tokens)
    end

    AM->>NM: Launch Containers (StartContainersRequest)
    NM->>NM: Execute Tasks (Mappers/Reducers inside CGroups)
    
    rect rgb(240, 240, 240)
        Note over RM, AM: Preemption Event (If prod queue needs capacity and default is over cap)
        RM->>AM: Notify Preemption request (Wait 15s grace period)
        AM->>AM: Save state & release container voluntarily
        Note over RM: If AM ignores, RM forcefully kills default container
    end

    AM->>RM: Unregister ApplicationMaster (FinishApplicationMasterRequest)
    RM->>NM: Cleanup Task Containers
